

HTML:

Add a scrolling wrapper class to define exactly what should be scrolling and where:
<section class="year-row fluid" id="t1960">
			<div class="clearfix">
				<div class="scrolling-wrapper">
					<img  class="year-tile" src="assets/images/dark-tiles/1960.png">
					<img src="assets/images/dark-tiles/1960x1.png">
					<img src="assets/images/dark-tiles/1960x2.png">
					<img src="assets/images/dark-tiles/1960x3.png">
					<img src="assets/images/dark-tiles/1960x4.png">
					<img src="assets/images/dark-tiles/1960x5.png">
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
    
    
    CSS:
   TEll the scrolling wrapper on which axis to scroll and not to wrap
    .scrolling-wrapper{
      overflow-x: scroll;
      overflow-y: hidden;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    Explicitly state that the images in here are inline-block
    .scrolling-wrapper .img {
        display: inline-block;
      }
